output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of English studies, one year after graduation, Education was the most common industry for White, Asian / Asian British and Mixed / Multiple ethnic groups ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities and Education were the most common industries for Black / African / Caribbean / Black British ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities, Education, Information and communication, Professional, scientific and technical activities and Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles were the most common industries for Other ethnic group ethnicity graduates, and Accommodation and food service activities, Education and Professional, scientific and technical activities were the most common industries for Unknown ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Information and communication where Other ethnic group ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion. The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Administrative and support service activities where White ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£19,300) and Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£13,900). The group with the highest earnings was Asian / Asian British ethnicity graduates who worked in the Public administration and defence - compulsory social security industry (median earnings of £25,700).
